# Django Backend Patterns

- Prefer service-layer orchestration for domain workflows (validation, state transitions, side effects), keeping views thin.
- Use explicit permission checks for staff-only and owner-only actions; do not infer role from client inputs.
- Keep DB writes in atomic transactions for critical flows (bids, publish, closure, settlement).
- Use idempotency for repeatable write operations where duplicate requests are likely (bid submit, payment callbacks).
- Emit asynchronous side effects (notifications, risk analysis, reconciliation) through Celery tasks after committed writes.
- Preserve API consistency with `/api/v1/` contracts and existing pagination strategy (page-number vs cursor for bids).
- Add or update tests when changing business rules in bidding, review/publish workflow, payments, or settlement.
